  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The governing requirement is documented in the inline requirement object (https://uofa.net/morrison/req/hemolysis-rh-criterion) specifying RH < 1 relative to predicate device; however, the top-level profile binding for that requirement is handled narratively under the Minimal profile conformance level.",
